news.title: Indore proposes 25.95% growth in collector's guideline for next financial year
news.para: The process of determining the govt guideline rates for immovable properties in Indore district, effective from April 1, is underway.

news.title: Chandigarh administration considers property tax rebates for those installing solar panels
news.para: This initiative, in collaboration with the municipal corporation, aims to encourage the residents to install solar panels under the PM's Suryaghar scheme.

news.title: Gujarat home loan disbursals fell 20% in Q3 FY25: SLBC data
news.para: Banking sector sources and real estate industry insiders attribute the dip to a number of factors including rising property prices, policy uncertainty, liquidity issues and shifting investor sentiment.

news.title: House of Abhinandan Lodha to buy land in 13 new cities
news.para: The House of Abhinandan Lodha currently has presence in Maharashtra, Goa, Uttar Pradesh, Punjab, and Himachal Pradesh.

news.title: Maharashtra government plans to make precast construction mandatory for real estate firms
news.para: Precast construction will encourage builders and contractors to get readymade components from outside the city instead of on-site activities and help them to continue work without adversely affecting the climate.

news.title: CBI books landlord, builder, buyers & bank staff in Rs 5.5 crore home loan fraud in Chennai
news.para: Bank-empanelled valuers M Vijayakumar and M S Senthil then submitted reports saying the property was worth 6.3 crore, following which a housing loan of 4.26 crore was sanctioned.

news.title: Court rejects CBI chargesheet against IHFL, DB Realty promoters in loan fraud case
news.para: The case involved Yes Bank, then led by Rana Kapoor, providing Rs 4,733 crore to DHFL, whose promoters Kapil Wadhawan and Dheeraj Wadhawan transferred Rs 678 crore to builder Sanjay Chhabariaa's FIIPL

news.title: UP-RERA moves NCLAT against NCLT orders on CIRP against Ansal API
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA said that the Ansal API had been evading its responsibilities to complete its projects and to comply with the orders of the authority.

news.title: Dakshina Kannada reports 173 illegal sand extraction cases in 10 months
news.para: In these cases, 107 trucks, 91 boats, six motor machines, one dredging machine, and 13 gas cylinders used for the purpose were seized. A total of 82 cases are pending before the courts. Officials collected a penalty amounting to Rs 54 lakh.

news.title: Consider plea to prevent illegal sand mining: Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing a public interest litigation filed by Pandi Yogeswaran. The petitioner also sought action against those involved in illegal sand mining in the pond.

news.title: HC strikes down section of Goa's town and country planning act
news.para: ​Three citizen organisations had filed a public interest litigation (PIL) in the HC contending that section 17 (2) of the Act was "mutilating" the Regional Plan.

news.title: China: Country Garden Services expects net profit of two billion yuan in 2024
news.para: Country Garden Services said it benefited from optimising some businesses it had acquired previously that led to lower impairment charges for the year ended 2024.

news.title: Citizens' feedback sought on proposed property rates in Bhopal
news.para: ​​ Local MLA Bhagwandas Sabnani, who opposed the revision of collector guideline rates in the previous year along with Bhopal MP Alok Sharma and CREDAI, was also present at the meeting.

news.title: Goa RERA orders builder to refund Rs 20.5 lakh for delayed flat, imposes fine
news.para: ​The builder, Expat Projects & Development Pvt Ltd, must pay back the money within 30 days along with interest of 11.1% per annum since 2018. RERA also awarded an additional Rs 1 lakh to the purchaser, which the builder must pay within 30 days.

news.title: Unregistered homestays must complete registration: Kodagu DC
news.para: During a meeting with district hospitality sector representatives, he discussed tourist safety measures. He highlighted the simplified homestay registration process, noting quick document verification and certificate issuance.

news.title: Madurai’s ageing housing complexes raise safety concerns
news.para: The decades-old structures at Race Course Colony, Chokkikulam, DRO Colony, and Pykara—built between 1964 and 1987—are crumbling due to poor maintenance, forcing many residents to vacate.

news.title: Kerala government urges centre to drop PMAY branding mandate
news.para: ​Local self-govt and excise minister MB Rajesh raised this concern during a meeting with Union housing and urban affairs minister Manohar Lal Khattar. Rajesh argued that the branding requirement affects beneficiaries' dignity and self-respect.

news.title: Karnataka: Supply power to only buildings with OCs, KERC tells Bescom
news.para: In its Dec 17, 2024 judgment, Supreme Court had also mandated that completion certificates be issued to new buildings only if the sanctioned plan is adhered to and violations, if any, are rectified.

news.title: Odisha court orders disbursement of Rs 450 crore to investors of scam-hit Rose Valley group
news.para: ​The special PMLA court in Bhubaneswar has ordered the release of Rs 332.76 crore of proceeds of crime, whose present value is Rs 450 crore with interest, the Enforcement Department (ED) said in a statement.
